Hi, 

I see there are some methods where we have to use project prefix instead of project name or id? For instance, the following method can be called only via Prefix.

```
@decoApiCallAddDevKey               
@decoMakerApiCallWithArgs(['testsuitename', 'prefix'])
def getTestSuite(self):
```

So, I wanted to know if there is any method by which we can get the project prefix so that I can set that as a class variable and all my library functions can use that?

Just like all other fields do when input is inconvertable.
Surrounding frameworks would know nothing about bson.errors

```
class ObjectIdField(fields.Field):
    type_label = 'ObjectIdField'

    def to_representation(self, value):
        return smart_str(value)

    def to_internal_value(self, data):
        try:
            return ObjectId(data)
        except bson.errors.InvalidId as e:
            raise ValidationError(e)
```

@vangheem I'm puzzled. When I set a LESS variable through resources registry control panel, in the development mode it's properly applied for all bundles. When I build the bundles (TTW) for production mode, variables are applied at least for the plone-bundle, but not my barceloneta-derived bundle.

I looked into LESS->CSS-compilation in resourceregistry-pattern and it looked quite simple: all bundle builds get the same less-variables.js before less-compilation.

Any idea, what could be so much different in barcelona.plone.less when compared to plone.less so that variable-overrides are applied in development mode, but not in build?

